WEBVTT

1
00:00:14.961 --> 00:00:17.496
I grew up with my identical twin.
[AI] 我和同卵双胞胎一起长大。

2
00:00:18.281 --> 00:00:20.745
who was an incredibly loving brother.
[AI] 他是一个非常可爱的兄弟。

3
00:00:21.297 --> 00:00:27.981
Now. one thing about being a twin is. it makes you an expert at spotting favoritism.
[AI] 现在双胞胎的一个特点是。它使你成为发现偏袒的专家。

4
00:00:28.462 --> 00:00:34.895
If his cookie was even slightly bigger than my cookie. I had questions.
[AI] 如果他的饼干比我的饼干大一点。我有问题。

5
00:00:34.919 --> 00:00:37.337
And clearly. I wasn't starving.
[AI] 而且很清楚。我没有挨饿。

6
00:00:38.120 --> 00:00:40.122
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

7
00:00:40.693 --> 00:00:46.554
When I became a psychologist. I began to notice favoritism of a different kind;
[AI] 当我成为一名心理学家时。我开始注意到另一种偏袒；

8
00:00:46.578 --> 00:00:51.362
and that is. how much more we value the body than we do the mind.
[AI] 就是这样。我们对身体的重视程度比我们对思想的重视程度高。

9
00:00:52.007 --> 00:00:58.041
I spent nine years at university earning my doctorate in psychology.
[AI] 我在大学里呆了九年，获得了心理学博士学位。

10
00:00:58.065 --> 00:01:02.319
and I can't tell you how many people look at my business card and say.
[AI] 我不能告诉你有多少人看着我的名片说。

11
00:01:02.343 --> 00:01:06.663
"Oh -- a psychologist. So. not a real doctor."
[AI] “哦，一个心理学家。所以，不是一个真正的医生。”

12
00:01:08.029 --> 00:01:09.827
as if it should say that on my card.
[AI] 好像应该在我的名片上写上。

13
00:01:09.851 --> 00:01:14.262
[Dr. Guy Winch. Just a Psychologist (Not a Real Doctor)] (Laughter)
[AI] [盖伊·温奇博士，只是个心理学家（不是真正的医生）]（笑声）

14
00:01:14.772 --> 00:01:20.619
This favoritism we show the body over the mind -- I see it everywhere.
[AI] 这种偏袒我们表现出身体胜过思想——我到处都能看到。

15
00:01:21.538 --> 00:01:23.205
I recently was at a friend's house.
[AI] 我最近在一个朋友家。

16
00:01:23.229 --> 00:01:25.751
and their five-year-old was getting ready for bed.
[AI] 他们五岁的孩子正在准备睡觉。

17
00:01:25.775 --> 00:01:29.380
He was standing on a stool by the sink. brushing his teeth.
[AI] 他站在水池边的凳子上。刷牙。

18
00:01:29.404 --> 00:01:33.212
when he slipped and scratched his leg on the stool when he fell.
[AI] 他摔倒时在凳子上滑倒，划伤了腿。

19
00:01:33.816 --> 00:01:36.788
He cried for a minute. but then he got back up.
[AI] 他哭了一会儿。但后来他又站了起来。

20
00:01:36.812 --> 00:01:42.114
got back on the stool. and reached out for a box of Band-Aids to put one on his cut.
[AI] 回到凳子上。他伸手拿了一盒创可贴贴在伤口上。

21
00:01:42.870 --> 00:01:46.807
Now. this kid could barely tie his shoelaces.
[AI] 现在这孩子几乎连鞋带都系不上。

22
00:01:46.831 --> 00:01:51.258
but he knew you have to cover a cut so it doesn't become infected.
[AI] 但他知道你必须盖住伤口，这样伤口才不会被感染。

23
00:01:51.282 --> 00:01:54.618
and you have to care for your teeth by brushing twice a day.
[AI] 你必须每天刷牙两次来保养你的牙齿。

24
00:01:55.245 --> 00:01:58.165
We all know how to maintain our physical health
[AI] 我们都知道如何保持身体健康

25
00:01:58.189 --> 00:02:00.704
and how to practice dental hygiene. right?
[AI] 以及如何实践牙齿卫生。正当

26
00:02:00.728 --> 00:02:03.517
We've known it since we were five years old.
[AI] 我们从五岁起就知道了。

27
00:02:04.262 --> 00:02:08.886
But what do we know about maintaining our psychological health?
[AI] 但是我们对保持心理健康了解多少呢？

28
00:02:09.890 --> 00:02:11.068
Well. nothing.
[AI] 好没有什么

29
00:02:11.598 --> 00:02:15.388
What do we teach our children about emotional hygiene?
[AI] 关于情绪卫生，我们教孩子什么？

30
00:02:16.560 --> 00:02:17.765
Nothing.
[AI] 没有什么

31
00:02:18.587 --> 00:02:23.035
How is it that we spend more time taking care of our teeth
[AI] 为什么我们要花更多的时间来照顾我们的牙齿

32
00:02:23.415 --> 00:02:25.199
than we do our minds?
[AI] 而不是我们的思想？

33
00:02:26.022 --> 00:02:30.832
Why is it that our physical health is so much more important to us
[AI] 为什么我们的身体健康对我们如此重要

34
00:02:30.856 --> 00:02:32.525
than our psychological health?
[AI] 而不是我们的心理健康？

35
00:02:33.213 --> 00:02:38.603
We sustain psychological injuries even more often than we do physical ones.
[AI] 我们遭受心理伤害的次数甚至比身体伤害的次数还要多。

36
00:02:38.627 --> 00:02:42.833
injuries like failure or rejection or loneliness.
[AI] 失败、拒绝或孤独等伤害。

37
00:02:42.857 --> 00:02:45.628
And they can also get worse if we ignore them.
[AI] 如果我们忽视它们，它们也会变得更糟。

38
00:02:45.652 --> 00:02:48.542
and they can impact our lives in dramatic ways.
[AI] 它们可以戏剧性地影响我们的生活。

39
00:02:49.105 --> 00:02:53.285
And yet. even though there are scientifically proven techniques
[AI] 然而。即使有科学证明的技术

40
00:02:53.309 --> 00:02:57.202
we could use to treat these kinds of psychological injuries.
[AI] 我们可以用来治疗这种心理伤害。

41
00:02:57.623 --> 00:02:58.782
we don't.
[AI] 我们没有。

42
00:02:59.194 --> 00:03:01.735
It doesn't even occur to us that we should.
[AI] 我们甚至没有想到我们应该这样做。

43
00:03:02.254 --> 00:03:06.311
"Oh. you're feeling depressed? Just shake it off; it's all in your head."
[AI] “哦，你感到沮丧了吗？摆脱它吧，一切都在你的脑子里。”

44
00:03:07.010 --> 00:03:09.887
Can you imagine saying that to somebody with a broken leg:
[AI] 你能想象对一个断腿的人说：

45
00:03:09.911 --> 00:03:12.497
"Oh. just walk it off; it's all in your leg."
[AI] “哦，走吧，都在你的腿上。”

46
00:03:12.727 --> 00:03:14.672
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

47
00:03:15.069 --> 00:03:21.039
It is time we closed the gap between our physical and our psychological health.
[AI] 现在是我们弥合生理和心理健康之间差距的时候了。

48
00:03:21.063 --> 00:03:23.182
It's time we made them more equal.
[AI] 是时候让他们更加平等了。

49
00:03:24.205 --> 00:03:26.023
more like twins.
[AI] 更像双胞胎。

50
00:03:26.968 --> 00:03:30.741
Speaking of which. my brother is also a psychologist.
[AI] 说到这里。我哥哥也是一位心理学家。

51
00:03:30.765 --> 00:03:33.196
So he's not a real doctor. either.
[AI] 所以他不是一个真正的医生。任何一个

52
00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:34.948
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

53
00:03:35.528 --> 00:03:37.500
We didn't study together. though.
[AI] 我们没有一起学习。虽然

54
00:03:37.524 --> 00:03:41.915
In fact. the hardest thing I've ever done in my life
[AI] 事实上这是我一生中做过的最难的事

55
00:03:41.939 --> 00:03:44.685
is move across the Atlantic to New York City
[AI] 将跨越大西洋搬到纽约市

56
00:03:44.709 --> 00:03:46.596
to get my doctorate in psychology.
[AI] 为了拿到心理学博士学位。

57
00:03:47.518 --> 00:03:50.481
We were apart then for the first time in our lives.
[AI] 那是我们有生以来第一次分开。

58
00:03:50.505 --> 00:03:53.790
and the separation was brutal for both of us.
[AI] 分离对我们俩来说都是残酷的。

59
00:03:54.115 --> 00:03:57.362
But while he remained among family and friends.
[AI] 但当他和家人朋友待在一起的时候。

60
00:03:57.386 --> 00:03:59.443
I was alone in a new country.
[AI] 我独自一人在一个新的国家。

61
00:04:00.071 --> 00:04:01.791
We missed each other terribly.
[AI] 我们非常想念对方。

62
00:04:01.815 --> 00:04:04.968
but international phone calls were really expensive then.
[AI] 但是国际电话当时真的很贵。

63
00:04:04.992 --> 00:04:09.421
and we could only afford to speak for five minutes a week.
[AI] 我们每周只能讲五分钟。

64
00:04:10.279 --> 00:04:11.805
When our birthday rolled around.
[AI] 当我们的生日临近时。

65
00:04:11.829 --> 00:04:14.381
it was the first we wouldn't be spending together.
[AI] 这是我们第一次不在一起消费。

66
00:04:14.405 --> 00:04:19.241
We decided to splurge. and that week. we would talk for 10 minutes. (Laughter)
[AI] 我们决定挥霍一下。那一周。我们会谈10分钟。（众笑）

67
00:04:19.265 --> 00:04:23.329
I spent the morning pacing around my room. waiting for him to call --
[AI] 我整个上午都在房间里踱来踱去。等他打电话--

68
00:04:23.974 --> 00:04:29.068
and waiting ... and waiting. But the phone didn't ring.
[AI] 等待。。。等待。但是电话没有响。

69
00:04:29.945 --> 00:04:31.963
Given the time difference. I assumed.
[AI] 考虑到时差。我猜想。

70
00:04:31.987 --> 00:04:34.285
"OK. he's out with friends. he'll call later."
[AI] “好的。他和朋友出去了。他稍后会打电话的。”

71
00:04:34.309 --> 00:04:35.817
There were no cell phones then.
[AI] 那时没有手机。

72
00:04:36.625 --> 00:04:37.928
But he didn't.
[AI] 但他没有。

73
00:04:38.991 --> 00:04:43.495
And I began to realize that after being away for over 10 months.
[AI] 离开10个多月后，我开始意识到这一点。

74
00:04:44.073 --> 00:04:46.908
he no longer missed me the way I missed him.
[AI] 他不再像我想念他那样想念我了。

75
00:04:47.848 --> 00:04:50.351
I knew he would call in the morning.
[AI] 我知道他早上会打电话来。

76
00:04:50.375 --> 00:04:54.890
but that night was one of the saddest and longest nights of my life.
[AI] 但那晚是我一生中最悲伤、最漫长的夜晚之一。

77
00:04:56.537 --> 00:04:58.406
I woke up the next morning.
[AI] 我第二天早上醒来。

78
00:04:58.508 --> 00:05:04.634
I glanced down at the phone. and I realized I had kicked it off the hook when pacing the day before.
[AI] 我低头看了一眼电话。我意识到前一天我在踱步的时候把它踢开了。

79
00:05:06.432 --> 00:05:08.083
I stumbled out of bed.
[AI] 我跌跌撞撞地起床。

80
00:05:08.107 --> 00:05:11.320
I put the phone back on the receiver. and it rang a second later.
[AI] 我把电话放回听筒上。过了一会儿，电话铃响了。

81
00:05:11.584 --> 00:05:13.244
And it was my brother.
[AI] 是我哥哥。

82
00:05:13.268 --> 00:05:14.936
and boy. was he pissed.
[AI] 还有男孩。他很生气。

83
00:05:14.960 --> 00:05:17.164
(Laughter)
[AI] （众笑）

84
00:05:17.188 --> 00:05:20.438
It was the saddest and longest night of his life as well.
[AI] 这也是他一生中最悲伤、最漫长的夜晚。

85
00:05:20.946 --> 00:05:23.357
Now. I tried to explain what happened. but he said.
[AI] 现在我试图解释发生了什么事。但是他说。

86
00:05:23.381 --> 00:05:26.539
"I don't understand. If you saw I wasn't calling you.
[AI] “我不明白，如果你看到我没有给你打电话。

87
00:05:26.563 --> 00:05:29.379
why didn't you just pick up the phone and call me?"
[AI] 你为什么不拿起电话给我打电话？"

88
00:05:30.877 --> 00:05:34.174
He was right. Why didn't I call him?
[AI] 他是对的。我为什么不给他打电话？

89
00:05:35.007 --> 00:05:38.879
I didn't have an answer then. But I do today.
[AI] 当时我没有答案。但我今天有。

90
00:05:38.903 --> 00:05:42.681
and it's a simple one: loneliness.
[AI] 这很简单：孤独。

91
00:05:43.768 --> 00:05:47.817
Loneliness creates a deep psychological wound.
[AI] 孤独会造成深刻的心理创伤。

92
00:05:47.841 --> 00:05:51.541
one that distorts our perceptions and scrambles our thinking.
[AI] 一个扭曲我们的感知，扰乱我们思维的人。

93
00:05:52.048 --> 00:05:57.318
It makes us believe that those around us care much less than they actually do.
[AI] 这让我们相信，我们周围的人比他们实际关心的要少得多。

94
00:05:57.854 --> 00:06:00.148
It make us really afraid to reach out.
[AI] 这让我们真的不敢伸出援手。

95
00:06:00.172 --> 00:06:04.262
because why set yourself up for rejection and heartache
[AI] 因为为什么要让自己被拒绝和心痛

96
00:06:04.286 --> 00:06:07.339
when your heart is already aching more than you can stand?
[AI] 当你的心已经痛得无法忍受时？

97
00:06:08.252 --> 00:06:11.335
I was in the grips of real loneliness back then.
[AI] 那时候我真的很孤独。

98
00:06:11.359 --> 00:06:15.228
but I was surrounded by people all day. so it never occurred to me.
[AI] 但我整天都被人包围着。所以我从没想过。

99
00:06:16.093 --> 00:06:19.712
But loneliness is defined purely subjectively.
[AI] 但孤独的定义纯粹是主观的。

100
00:06:20.235 --> 00:06:25.999
It depends solely on whether you feel emotionally or socially disconnected
[AI] 这完全取决于你是在情感上还是在社交上感到脱节

101
00:06:26.023 --> 00:06:27.181
from those around you.
[AI] 来自你周围的人。

102
00:06:27.205 --> 00:06:28.362
And I did.
[AI] 我做到了。

103
00:06:29.069 --> 00:06:34.335
There is a lot of research on loneliness. and all of it is horrifying.
[AI] 有很多关于孤独的研究。所有这些都是可怕的。

104
00:06:35.319 --> 00:06:39.277
Loneliness won't just make you miserable; it will kill you.
[AI] 孤独不仅会让你痛苦；它会杀了你的。

105
00:06:39.610 --> 00:06:40.780
I'm not kidding.
[AI] 我不是开玩笑。

106
00:06:40.804 --> 00:06:44.395
Chronic loneliness increases your likelihood of an early death
[AI] 长期孤独会增加你早逝的可能性

107
00:06:44.419 --> 00:06:48.087
by 14 percent. Fourteen percent!
[AI] 增长14%。百分之十四！

108
00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:52.604
Loneliness causes high blood pressure. high cholesterol.
[AI] 孤独会导致高血压。高胆固醇。

109
00:06:52.628 --> 00:06:56.353
It even suppress the functioning of your immune system.
[AI] 它甚至会抑制你免疫系统的功能。

110
00:06:56.377 --> 00:07:00.409
making you vulnerable to all kinds of illnesses and diseases.
[AI] 使你容易患上各种疾病。

111
00:07:00.433 --> 00:07:03.971
In fact. scientists have concluded that taken together.
[AI] 事实上科学家们已经得出结论，综合起来。

112
00:07:03.995 --> 00:07:07.651
chronic loneliness poses as significant a risk
[AI] 长期孤独是一个巨大的风险

113
00:07:07.675 --> 00:07:11.816
for your long-term health and longevity as cigarette smoking.
[AI] 为了你的长期健康和长寿，就像吸烟一样。

114
00:07:12.284 --> 00:07:16.391
Now. cigarette packs come with warnings saying. "This could kill you."
[AI] 现在香烟包装上有警告语。“这会杀了你。”

115
00:07:16.853 --> 00:07:18.597
But loneliness doesn't.
[AI] 但孤独却不是。

116
00:07:19.225 --> 00:07:24.167
And that's why it's so important that we prioritize our psychological health.
[AI] 这就是为什么我们把心理健康放在首位是如此重要。

117
00:07:24.191 --> 00:07:26.893
that we practice emotional hygiene.
[AI] 我们练习情绪卫生。

118
00:07:27.345 --> 00:07:30.178
Because you can't treat a psychological wound
[AI] 因为你不能治疗心理创伤

119
00:07:30.202 --> 00:07:32.221
if you don't even know you're injured.
[AI] 如果你不知道自己受伤了。

120
00:07:33.896 --> 00:07:36.740
Loneliness isn't the only psychological wound
[AI] 孤独不是唯一的心理创伤

121
00:07:36.764 --> 00:07:39.653
that distorts our perceptions and misleads us.
[AI] 这扭曲了我们的观念，误导了我们。

122
00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:42.623
Failure does that as well.
[AI] 失败也是如此。

123
00:07:43.638 --> 00:07:45.901
I once visited a day care center.
[AI] 我曾经参观过一个日托中心。

124
00:07:45.925 --> 00:07:50.412
where I saw three toddlers play with identical plastic toys.
[AI] 我看到三个蹒跚学步的孩子玩着完全一样的塑料玩具。

125
00:07:50.960 --> 00:07:54.999
You had to slide the red button. and a cute doggie would pop out.
[AI] 你必须滑动红色按钮。一只可爱的小狗会跳出来。

126
00:07:55.637 --> 00:08:00.208
One little girl tried pulling the purple button. then pushing it.
[AI] 一个小女孩试着拉紫色按钮。然后推它。

127
00:08:00.232 --> 00:08:04.825
and then she just sat back and looked at the box with her lower lip trembling.
[AI] 然后她坐下来，看着盒子，下唇颤抖着。

128
00:08:04.849 --> 00:08:07.900
The little boy next to her watched this happen.
[AI] 她旁边的小男孩看着这一切发生。

129
00:08:07.924 --> 00:08:11.759
then turned to his box and burst into tears without even touching it.
[AI] 然后转向他的盒子，甚至连碰都没碰就哭了起来。

130
00:08:12.961 --> 00:08:16.403
Meanwhile. another little girl tried everything she could think of
[AI] 同时另一个小女孩想尽一切办法

131
00:08:16.427 --> 00:08:18.211
until she slid the red button.
[AI] 直到她按下红色按钮。

132
00:08:18.235 --> 00:08:21.713
the cute doggie popped out. and she squealed with delight.
[AI] 那只可爱的小狗突然跳了出来。她高兴得尖叫起来。

133
00:08:22.241 --> 00:08:26.029
So: three toddlers with identical plastic toys.
[AI] 所以：三个蹒跚学步的孩子有着相同的塑料玩具。

134
00:08:26.053 --> 00:08:29.164
but with very different reactions to failure.
[AI] 但对失败的反应却截然不同。

135
00:08:29.713 --> 00:08:33.608
The first two toddlers were perfectly capable of sliding a red button.
[AI] 头两个蹒跚学步的孩子完全能够滑动红色按钮。

136
00:08:34.275 --> 00:08:37.386
The only thing that prevented them from succeeding
[AI] 唯一阻止他们成功的事

137
00:08:37.410 --> 00:08:41.085
was that their mind tricked them into believing they could not.
[AI] 是他们的思想欺骗了他们，使他们相信他们不能。

138
00:08:41.740 --> 00:08:45.444
Now. adults get tricked this way as well. all the time.
[AI] 现在成年人也会被这种方式欺骗。总是

139
00:08:45.848 --> 00:08:51.001
In fact. we all have a default set of feelings and beliefs
[AI] 事实上我们都有一套默认的感觉和信念

